<UserControl
    xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
    xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
	xmlns:shared="http://schemas.actiprosoftware.com/winfx/xaml/shared" 
	xmlns:editor="http://schemas.actiprosoftware.com/winfx/xaml/syntaxeditor" 
	xmlns:editors="http://schemas.actiprosoftware.com/winfx/xaml/editors" 
	xmlns:sample="clr-namespace:ActiproSoftware.ProductSamples.SyntaxEditorSamples.QuickStart.AdornmentsWatermark"
    >

	<editor:SyntaxEditor x:Name="editor">
			<editor:EditorDocument x:Name="document" xml:space="preserve">
				<editor:EditorDocument.Language>
					<sample:CustomSyntaxLanguage />
				</editor:EditorDocument.Language><![CDATA[This QuickStart shows how to create an adornment manager that renders
a watermark effect in the editor view.  The watermark remains
affixed to the center of the view, even when the editor is
resized.

This sort of feature is useful when wanting to display "evaluation"
or other messages in the background of the editor.

The adornment manager is created by the syntax language assigned to
this editor's document.
]]></editor:EditorDocument>
	</editor:SyntaxEditor>
	
</UserControl>
